        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 4:23PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pine Tree Junction, or 17 miles southwest of Wright, moving east at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pine Tree Junction and Pumpkin Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
